New Records: Cody Bellinger hit a home run in the second inning, his 14th of the season.
Keegan Thompson recorded his second save of the season by striking out Dylan Crews to end the game.
Key Match Events: Cody Bellinger hit a solo home run in the bottom of the second inning, scoring Michael Busch and extending the Cubs' lead.
Keegan Thompson threw a walk-off strikeout in the bottom of the ninth inning to end the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Nationals Park with an attendance of 28,792.
